---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'SafetyWing in Canada', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage', text: 'What SafetyWing Covers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'limitations', text: 'Limitations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'waiting-period', text: 'For the Waiting Period', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose SafetyWing', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Canada', href: '/countries/canada/insurance' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing vs Cigna', href: '/compare/safetywing-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Nomad Insurance', coverage: 'Travel medical', price: '$45-70/mo' },
  { plan: 'Remote Health', coverage: 'Health insurance', price: '$200-280/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing in Canada"
  description="Guide to using SafetyWing in Canada. Popular travel medical insurance for the waiting period and short-term visitors."
  headline="SafetyWing in Canada"
  subheadline="Popular travel medical insurance for the waiting period. Budget-friendly but limited coverage."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/canada-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a SafetyWing Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/safetywing"
>
  <h2 id="overview">SafetyWing in Canada</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is a popular choice for covering Canada's 3-month provincial healthcare waiting period. At $45-70/month, it provides affordable emergency coverage while you wait for provincial eligibility.
  </p>
  <p>
    However, Canada's high healthcare costs make understanding SafetyWing's limitations essential. It's travel medical insurance, not comprehensive health coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$45/mo</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Starting price</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$250K</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Maximum coverage</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$250</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Deductible</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Quick Coverage for the Waiting Period"
    description="SafetyWing is easy to purchase and starts immediately."
    buttonText="Get SafetyWing"
    buttonHref="/go/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage">What SafetyWing Covers</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing Nomad Insurance includes:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Emergency medical:</strong> Up to $250,000</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital stays:</strong> Covered after $250 deductible</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency dental:</strong> Pain relief and emergency care</li>
    <li><strong>Medical evacuation:</strong> $100,000</li>
    <li><strong>Trip interruption:</strong> Some coverage included</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>How It Works in Canada</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing operates on a reimbursement basis. You pay for care upfront and submit claims for reimbursement. Given Canada's costs, this means potentially significant out-of-pocket expenses before reimbursement.
  </p>

  <h2 id="limitations">Limitations</h2>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">What SafetyWing Doesn't Cover</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
      <li><strong>Pre-existing conditions:</strong> Completely excluded</li>
      <li><strong>Routine care:</strong> Checkups, preventive care not covered</li>
      <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Not covered</li>
      <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> Not covered (except emergency complications)</li>
      <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Ongoing treatment not covered</li>
      <li><strong>Dental (routine):</strong> Not covered</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Canada Cost Context</h3>
  <p>
    Canada's healthcare costs make SafetyWing's limitations significant:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>ER visit:</strong> $500-1,500 out of pocket</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital day:</strong> $1,000-3,000 out of pocket</li>
    <li><strong>Specialist:</strong> $200-500 out of pocket</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is for emergencies only. Routine care will cost you full price.
  </p>

  <h2 id="waiting-period">For the Waiting Period</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing works as a budget option for the 3-month provincial healthcare waiting period if you're:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Young and healthy</li>
    <li>Have no pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>Comfortable with emergency-only coverage</li>
    <li>Willing to pay out-of-pocket for routine care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Consider More Comprehensive Options</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      For the waiting period, some Canadian insurers offer specific "waiting period" plans with broader coverage. If you have health concerns or want peace of mind, these may be worth the extra cost.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance vs Remote Health</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Nomad Insurance ($45/mo):</strong> Travel medical. Suitable for waiting period if healthy.</li>
    <li><strong>Remote Health ($200+/mo):</strong> Actual health insurance. Better for longer stays or ongoing coverage needs.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose SafetyWing in Canada</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Healthy new arrivals (waiting period)</li>
        <li>Short-term visitors</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious travelers</li>
        <li>Those with no pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Young, healthy individuals</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Anyone with health conditions</li>
        <li>Those needing mental health care</li>
        <li>Families with children</li>
        <li>Long-term residents</li>
        <li>Those uncomfortable with gaps</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>The Bottom Line</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing works for healthy individuals covering the waiting period on a budget. For longer stays or health concerns, invest in comprehensive international health insurance.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Need More Than SafetyWing?"
    description="Compare comprehensive international health insurance for Canada."
    buttonText="See All Options"
    buttonHref="/countries/canada/insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance with limitations. Canada's high healthcare costs mean out-of-pocket expenses can be significant.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
